  <div class="px-4 md:px-0 md:mx-4 md:w-6/12 lg:w-5/12 mw:w-4/12">
    <p>
      What makes the ability so strange and difficult to use is it's very unclear visuals. The visuals show a large circle, indicating that anything in it's circle will be affected. In practice this is a little different. Only areas in line of sight of the center of Blizzard are affected. Meaning that anyone behind cover or walls will not be frozen. In the image you can see it in action. <strong>Any of the red areas are unaffected</strong>, even though the visuals are absolutely covering the area. This also goes for vertical line of sight. So if the enemy would be behind a wall, but his head pokes out above it, he will still be affected. In other words, as long as any part of the hero is within a green zone, he will be affected. This also goes for the very edge of the ultimate. <strong>The payload, shields, and breakable objects do not block line of sight of Blizzard</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      Unfortunately this can often lead to unexpected escapes from enemies. Things like small lanerns, or other objects, can block line of sight and set enemies free. This can be very frustrating, but it's something we will have to deal with.
    </p>

    <p>
      The area that Blizzard covers is spherical. Because of this is it very difficult to hit targets in the air, as they are more likely to be ouside the area.
    </p>

